<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 9000 Pro Sleeper After 05/01/1997, and 9800 Model After 07/01/1997 -
        REMOVE AND INSTALL - BLOWER MOTOR ASSEMBLy - Sleeper Compartment (9800)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1602016" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>BLOWER MOTOR ASSEMBLy - Sleeper Compartment (9800)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch and A/C switch are OFF.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover from bunk blower housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602041">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1602041" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 44. Bunk Blower Housing Cover (9800)</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connector for the blower motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the five screws that secure the blower motor assembly in the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602042">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the blower motor assembly from the housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602042" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Screws Holding Blower Motor Assembly in Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the motor is to be replaced, remove the spring clip from the end of the motor shaft
                    and slide the blower wheel off the shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the blower motor resistor assembly is to be replaced, remove it at this time from
                    inside the blower motor housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the motor was replaced, slide the blower wheel onto the motor shaft and secure in
                    place with the spring clip removed in Step 6 of Remove above.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the blower motor resistor assembly, if removed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the blower motor into the blower motor housing using the five screws removed in
                    Step 4 of Remove above (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602042">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the electrical connector to the motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test the motor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install cover on blower housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602041">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
